lass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104two1665703130263.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/two1665703130263.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/two1665703130263.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"two1665703130263\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      trigger erase\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Trigger that deletes all occurrences currently in the component, both in the external structure, and in the database. This is a very dangerous trigger—use it with extreme care!\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"two1665703130263__section_w61ab1b7b1_w62ab1b7_w63ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"two1665703130263__table_d14462e1_d14463e1_d14464e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Declaration:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">trigger erase</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Applies to:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activation:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Activated by the ^ERASE structure editor function.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default behavior:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Behavior upon completion:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n None\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"two1665703130263__section_w64ab1b7b3_w65ab1b7_w66ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d108327e129\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"two1665703130263__p_d117074e1_d117075e1_d117076e1\">The erase trigger can be used to delete retrieved data from the database. The actual deletion of data is activated by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">erase</span> statement, which should be placed in this trigger.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"two1665703130263__note_w67ab1b7b3b5_w68ab1b7b3_w69ab1b7_w70ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The erase trigger\n            can delete all data that has been retrieved into the component, which makes it very\n            dangerous to use. Consider disabling the erase trigger by omitting the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">erase</span> statement, or use it with extreme care.</div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"two1665703130263__note_w71ab1b7b3b7_w72ab1b7b3_w73ab1b7_w74ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> As an alternative to erasing data, you can clear data from the form. The ^CLEAR structure editor function is safer than ^ERASE because it removes data from the form, but does not delete data stored in the database.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"two1665703130263__p_d117077e1_d117078e1_d117079e1\">The process flow for the erase trigger is as follows:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"two1665703130263__li_d44552e1_d44553e1_d44554e1\">The ^ERASE structure editor function activates the erase trigger.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"two1665703130263__li_d44555e1_d44556e1_d44557e1\">Uniface activates the delete trigger for each occurrence retrieved from the database.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"two1665703130263__li_d44558e1_d44559e1_d44560e1\">For each occurrence, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">delete</span> statement in the delete trigger deletes the occurrence from the database.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"two1665703130263__section_gg4_vqg_fcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d108327e169\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">erase</span> in the erase Trigger</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"ph\">The ^ERASE function can be\n                  quite drastic.</span> It is common to disable the erase trigger by omitting the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">erase</span> statement from it, or to ask for confirmation for the\n               drastic action of erasing all occurrences. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"two1665703130263__pre_e1l_wqg_fcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger erase ; of component\nif ($totocc(CUSTOMER) &gt;= 1)\n askmess \"%%$totocc(CUSTOMER) occurrences. Erase them all?\"\n if ($status = 0)\n return\n endif\nendif\nerase\nif ($status &lt;0)\n message \"Erase error; see message frame\"\n rollback\nelse\n if ($status = 1)\n message \"Erase is not allowed\"\n else\n message \"Erase was successful\"\n commit\n if($status &lt; 0)\n rollback\n endif\n endif\nendif\nend ; erase \n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aag1665703130023.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger clear</a><p>Trigger that reacts to the user's request to start over with a clean form.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfn1665703129379.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger delete</a><p>Removes occurrences marked for deletion, when writing updates to the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qol1665703129540.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>trigger lock</a><p>System trigger that is activated for cautious and optimistic locking when modifying or writing a database occurrence. It is the location for the lock statement and associated logic.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532562\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532562\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "trigger erase Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 trigger erase Trigger that deletes all occurrences currently in the component, both in the external structure, and in the database. This is a very dangerous trigger—use it with extreme care! Declaration: trigger erase Applies to: Form Activation: Activated by the ^ERASE structure editor function. Default behavior: None Behavior upon completion: None Description The erase trigger can be used to delete retrieved data from the database. The actual deletion of data is activated by the erase statement, which should be placed in this trigger. CAUTION: The erase trigger can delete all data that has been retrieved into the component, which makes it very dangerous to use. Consider disabling the erase trigger by omitting the erase statement, or use it with extreme care. Note: As an alternative to erasing data, you can clear data from the form. The ^CLEAR structure editor function is safer than ^ERASE because it removes data from the form, but does not delete data stored in the database. The process flow for the erase trigger is as follows: The ^ERASE structure editor function activates the erase trigger. Uniface activates the delete trigger for each occurrence retrieved from the database. For each occurrence, the delete statement in the delete trigger deletes the occurrence from the database. Example: Using erase in the erase Trigger The ^ERASE function can be quite drastic. It is common to disable the erase trigger by omitting the erase statement from it, or to ask for confirmation for the drastic action of erasing all occurrences. For example: trigger erase ; of component if ($totocc(CUSTOMER) >= 1) askmess \"%%$totocc(CUSTOMER) occurrences. Erase them all?\" if ($status = 0) return endif endif erase if ($status <0) message \"Erase error; see message frame\" rollback else if ($status = 1) message \"Erase is not allowed\" else message \"Erase was successful\" commit if($status < 0) rollback endif endif endif end ; erase Copy Related Links trigger clear Trigger that reacts to the user's request to start over with a clean form. trigger delete Removes occurrences marked for deletion, when writing updates to the database. trigger lock System trigger that is activated for cautious and optimistic locking when modifying or writing a database occurrence. It is the location for the lock statement and associated logic. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}